# <type>[optional scope][!]: <description>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]
#
# Examples:
#   feat(installer): add profile-based install planning
#   fix(hooks): preserve colored WIP warnings
#   docs: update installer usage notes
#   refactor(prompt)!: simplify prompt state handling
#
# Types:
#   feat:     A new feature
#   fix:      A bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation-only changes
#   style:    Formatting or style changes that do not affect behavior
#   refactor: Code changes that neither fix a bug nor add a feature
#   perf:     Performance improvements
#   test:     Adding or updating tests
#   build:    Build system or dependency changes
#   ci:       CI configuration or script changes
#   chore:    Maintenance tasks that do not change runtime behavior
#   revert:   Revert a previous commit
#
# Guidelines:
#   - Use the imperative mood: "add", "fix", "update", not "added" or "fixes".
#   - Keep the subject concise, ideally 72 characters or less.
#   - Add a blank line before body text.
#   - Explain why in the body when the subject is not enough.
#   - Use "!" after the type/scope for breaking changes.
#   - Document breaking changes with a footer:
#       BREAKING CHANGE: describe the required migration
#
# Footer examples:
#   Closes #123
#   Refs #456
#   BREAKING CHANGE: config files now load from XDG_CONFIG_HOME
